ring [[Sasha Grey]] gained notoriety for the studio brand when Kulich offered a portion of the proceeds to the [[National Education Association]] and the donation was rejected.<ref name=thp>{{cite news|title=Sasha Grey Filmmaker To Donate 'Anal Artists' Proceeds To Read Across America, NEA Declines|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/02/06/sasha-grey-porn-school-read-across-america-nea_n_1258161.html|publisher=[[The Huffington Post]]|accessdate=31 March 2013|first=Emmeline|last=Zhao|date=6 February 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2012, Monarchy launched 'OGEE Studios' on the heels of the success of Assence Films.<ref>{{cite web|title=Monarchy Distribution Teams up with Exile for OGEE Studios|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Monarchy-Distribution-Teams-up-with-Exile-for-OGEE-Studios-466224.html|publisher=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|accessdate=31 March 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2012, Monarchy announced that they had signed a deal with Blue Coyote Pictures to handle the distribution for a new [[Transsexual]] line called Tranny Factory.<ref>{{cite web|title=Monarchy Distribution Inks Deal with Blue Coyote|url=http://business.avn.com/company-news/Monarchy-Distribution-Inks-Deal-with-Blue-Coyote-472184.html|publisher=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2012, Kulich gained notoriety when he offered an [[adult film]] offer to [[Valeria Lukyanova]], the Ukrainian model who resembles a real life barbie doll. Lukyanova never responded to the $10,000 offer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Monarchy Makes Porn Offer to Ukrainian 'Living Barbie'|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Monarchy-Makes-Porn-Offer-to-Ukrainian-Living-Barbie-485847.html|publisher=[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]|accessdate=1 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the [[Go Daddy]] commercial for [[Super Bowl XLVII]] starring [[Bar Refaeli]] and [[Jesse Heiman]], Kulich made an offer to Heiman to appear in an adult film. Heiman refused, stating he would hold out for ''[[Playgirl]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jesse Heiman, Bar Refaeli's Kissing Partner, Gets Offer To Make Porn|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/05/jesse-heiman-porn-offer_n_2624749.html|work=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=1 April 2013|date=5 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2012, Earlie Johnson of [[Muskegon, Michigan]]'s house was burglarized and his $7500 porn collection was stolen. Kulich stepped up to replace the collection.<ref>{{cite news|title=Earlie Johnson's Stolen Porn Collection Replenished By Porn Companies|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/26/earlie-johnsons-stolen-porn_n_2766196.html|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=1 April 2013|date=26 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn July, 2013 after TheDirty.com broke a story that [[Anthony Weiner]] had been caught sexting and involved in inappropriate conduct, Kulich announced that he was producing a movie entitled \"Don't Pull Out\" in which 15% of the proceeds would be donated to Weiner's campaign.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pornographer Mike Kulich Vows To Raise Money For Anthony Weiner With 'Don't Pull Out' DVD|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/07/24/anthony-weiner-dont-pull-out-dvd_n_3645135.html?1374689879|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=26 July 2013|date=24 July 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013, [[IAC/InterActiveCorp|IAC]] PR Executive [[Justine Sacco]] tweeted \"Going to Africa. Hope I don\u2019t get AIDS. Just kidding. I\u2019m white!\u201d The tweet spiraled out of control and went viral and trending on Twitter for more than 2 days. Kulich reached out to Sacco offering a role in a film entitled \"Justine's African Vacation\" offering her 5 interracial scenes for $10,000 and 10% of the movies profits.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kulich Offers 'Ashamed' Ex-PR Exec a Porn Opp|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=172832|publisher=[[XBIZ]]|accessdate=29 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230235644/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=172832|archive-date=30 December 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, Kulich announced the launch of [[Skweez Media]], a new VOD site catering to Adult Entertainment.\n\nIn February 2014, a film titled ''The Real Housewives of Westport'' was released. It is based on Kulich's hometown: [[Westport, Connecticut|Westport]], [[Connecticut]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://06880danwoog.com/2014/01/10/the-real-housewives-of-westport/|title=The Real Housewives Of Westport|publisher=06880: Where Westport meets the world|date=January 10, 2014|accessdate=January 17, 2014|author=Dan Woog}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2014, Kulich announced that he had launched Stunner PR, a full service publicity firm catering to Adult Entertainment Companies and Adult Performers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=174506|title=Monarchy Distribution Owner Mike Kulich Launches Stunner PR|publisher=XBIZ|date=February 6, 2014|accessdate=June 6, 2014|author=XBIZ|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304025344/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=174506|archive-date=March 4, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Death ==\n\nOn September 24, 2016, Kulich was found dead at his home in Los Angeles. Mike is survived by his ex-wife Michelle Burr and their young son Tyler Kulich, who just one month before his death had finished a 3+ year battle with  Accute Lymphoblastic Leukemia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.westport-news.com/news/article/Westport-porn-mogul-dead-at-29-9289074.php|title=Westport porn mogul dead at 29}}</ref><ref>http://www.westportnow.com/index.php?/v3/obitjump/mike_kulich_29/</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Asses For The Masses''\n| [[Nightmoves]] ''Best All Sex/Gonzo''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Superstars''\n| [[Nightmoves]] ''Best All Sex/Gonzo''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Tranny Hookups''\n| [[Nightmoves]] ''Best Transsexual Release''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Assence Films''\n| [[AVN Award]] ''Best New Studio''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Chocolate Yam Yams ''\n