 {{ubl|Feras Antoon|David Marmorstein Tassillo<ref>{{cite web|last1=Auerbach|first1=David|title=Vampire Porn|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technology/2014/10/mindgeek_porn_monopoly_its_dominance_is_a_cautionary_tale_for_other_industries.html|website=Slate|accessdate=19 December 2014|date=23 October 2014|quote=Thylman was bought out by current CEO Ferras Antoon and COO David Tassillo, longtime players within the company, who now control operations from Montreal.}}</ref>}}\n| members = \n| num_employees = \u22481400 (2016)<ref>{{cite web|title=Bureau de d\u00e9cision et de r\u00e9vision|url=https://lautorite.qc.ca/fileadmin/lautorite/bulletin/2016/vol13no20/vol13no20_2.pdf|website=lautorite.qc.ca|publisher=Autorit\u00e9 des march\u00e9s financiers|accessdate=16 April 2018|page=45|date=19 May 2016|quote={{lang|fr|Le groupe Mindgeek est une entreprise priv\u00e9e qui emploie approximativement 1 400 personnes \u00e0 temps plein dans le monde, dont un nombre important \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al.}}|language=French}}</ref>\n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = {{hlist|[[Brazzers]]|[[Digital Playground]]|[[Men.com]]|[[Mofos]]|[[Reality Kings]]|[[Sean Cody]]|[[Twistys]]|[[WhyNotBi.com]]|<small>[[#Global_Alexa_ranks|Global Alexa ranks]]</small>}}\n| website = {{URL|mindgeek.com}}\n| footnotes = \n| bodystyle = \n}}\n\n'''MindGeek Holding SARL''' (formerly '''Manwin''') is a privately held Canadian company<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://plus.lapresse.ca/screens/5af271ce-5112-411d-8502-319e5d5fa7e7__7C__2tXW0KGJgOr7.html|title=Porno et imp\u00f4ts - L'\u00e9nigme Mindgeek, du Luxembourg \u00e0 Montr\u00e9al|last=Bergeron|first=Maxime|date=10 October 2016|work=La Presse+|access-date=30 May 2018|language=fr-CA|trans-title=Porn and taxes - The Mindgeek Enigma, from Luxembourg to Montreal}}</ref> that focuses primarily on [[Internet pornography]].<ref name=\"The Geek-Kings of Smut page 5\">{{cite web|last1=Wallace|first1=Benjamin|title=The Geek-Kings of Smut|url=http://nymag.com/news/features/70985/index4.html|website=New York Magazine|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141010205213/http://nymag.com/news/features/70985/index4.html|archivedate=10 October 2014|page=5|date=30 January 2011}}</ref> Though legally registered in Luxembourg, it operates mainly from Canada<ref name=\":0\">[[Canadian House of Commons Standing Committee on Health|HESA]], [http://www.ourcommons.ca/DocumentViewer/en/42-1/HESA/meeting-50/evidence Evidence], 1st Session, 42nd Parliament, 11 April 2017, 1110 (Dr. Gail Dines, President, Culture Reframed). \"''Although MindGeek is headquartered in Luxembourg, with offices across the USA and Europe, 800 of its more than 1,000 employees work from their Montreal office.''\"</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://plus.lapresse.ca/screens/e8eec84a-870e-4cfe-8bc0-3e3b5b918515__7C__pTd61friXs-d.html|title=Deux Rois De La Porno Parmi Les Cibles De L'amf|last=Vailles|first=Francis|date=24 March 2016|work=La Presse+|access-date=16 April 2018|language=fr-CA|quote=Parmi les hommes d\u2019affaires que l\u2019Autorit\u00e9 des march\u00e9s financiers (AMF) a dans sa ligne de mire figurent Feras Antoon et Mark Wael Antoon, qui g\u00e8rent depuis Montr\u00e9al l\u2019un des plus grands r\u00e9seaux de sites pornographiques au monde. Feras Antoon est copropri\u00e9taire de la soci\u00e9t\u00e9 MindGeek avec David Tassillo. Le fr\u00e8re de Feras, Mark, en est l\u2019un des vice-pr\u00e9sidents.}}</ref> with headquarters in [[Montreal]] and additional offices in [[Dublin]], [[London]], [[Hamburg]], [[Bucharest]], [[Nicosia]], [[Los Angeles]], [[Miami]], and [[San Diego]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mindgeek.com/contact/|title=Contact Us|last=MindGeek|date=17 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=MindGeek S.A R.L.: Private Company Information |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=142431065 |website=Bloomberg.com |accessdate=10 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Contact Us |url=https://www.mindgeek.com/contact/ |website=mindgeek.com |accessdate=4 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nMindGeek owns and operates many popular [[pornography|pornographic]] websites,<ref>{{cite news|first1=Jim Waterson Media|last1=editor|accessdate=16 March 2019|title=UK online pornography age block triggers privacy fears|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2019/mar/16/uk-online-porn-age-verification-launch|newspaper=The Guardian|date=16 March 2019|issn=0261-3077|via=theguardian.com}}</ref> including [[Video hosting service|video sharing services]] [[Pornhub]], [[RedTube]], and [[YouPorn]], as well as [[Pornographic film|adult film]] production companies [[Brazzers]], [[Digital Playground]], [[Men.com]], [[WhyNotBi.com]], [[Reality Kings]], and [[Sean Cody]], among others.<ref name=\"Vampire Porn\">{{cite web|last1=Auerbach|first1=David|title=Vampire Porn|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technology/2014/10/mindgeek_porn_monopoly_its_dominance_is_a_cautionary_tale_for_other_industries.html|website=Slate|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219160919/http://www.slate.com/articles/technology/technology/2014/10/mindgeek_porn_monopoly_its_dominance_is_a_cautionary_tale_for_other_industries.html|archivedate=19 December 2014|date=23 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nMindGeek has its origins in Mansef and Interhub (owners of Brazzers and Pornhub respectively). Mansef was founded in 2004 by Stephane Manos and Ouissam Youssef in Montreal. Interhub was founded in 2007 by Matt Keezer and Mansef. Internet entrepreneur [[Fabian Thylmann]] bought both companies in 2010, changed their name to Manwin, and went on an acquisition spree thereafter with financing from Colbeck Capital to buy out many other popular pornographic websites.<ref>{{cite newspaper |title=How a (Canadian-founded) company you\u2019ve never heard of took control of the porn industry |newspaper=National Post |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/how-a-canadian-founded-company-youve-never-heard-of-took-control-of-the-porn-industry |accessdate=8 January 2020 |date=24 October 2014 |language=en-CA}}</ref> Thylmann later sold his stake in Manwin, after coming under tax evasion charges,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/international/2015/09/26/naked-capitalism|title=Naked capitalism|last=|first=|date=26 Sep 2015|work=The Economist|access-date=10 July 2018|language=en}}</ref> to the senior management of the company in Montreal composed of [[Feras Antoon]] and David Marmorstein, who later changed the company's name to MindGeek.\n\nIt is the largest pornographic company owning both free and paid websites, an advertising network, and major professional porn studios and as such has garnered criticism for having detrimental effects on the porn industry due to its monopolistic control of the supply chain. The company has both brought and defended copyright lawsuits for hosting pirated content.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/michaelthomsen/2015/11/30/mindgeek-is-both-plaintiff-and-defendant-in-two-new-dmca-lawsuits/#4ae8f94734e6|title=MindGeek Is Both Plaintiff And Defendant In Two New DMCA Lawsuits|last=Thomsen|first=Michael|work=Forbes|access-date=3 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> \n\nMindGeek is a member of the [[Association of Sites Advocating Child Protection]] and uses the \"Restricted To Adults\" label to identify its pornographic websites.\n\n==History==\n\n===Origins and early history===\nIn the late 1990s, German-born [[Fabian Thylmann]] created [[Too Much Media|NATS]] (Next-Generation Affiliate Tracking Software), which was used for marketing pornography across different websites.<ref name=\"'King of Porn' arrested on charges of avoiding paying tax on the \u00a360million profits from his online sex empire\">{{cite web|last1=Reynolds|first1=Emma|title='King of Porn' arrested on charges of avoiding paying tax on the \u00a360million profits from his online sex empire|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2249296/King-Porn-Fabian-Thylmann-arrested-charges-avoiding-paying-tax.html|website=Daily Mail Online|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130422051111/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2249296/King-Porn-Fabian-Thylmann-arrested-charges-avoiding-paying-tax.html|archivedate=22 April 2013|date=20 December 2012}}</ref> In 2006, Thylmann sold his shares in the company that controlled NATS and used the proceeds to purchase the Privat Amateure website.<ref name=\"Harnessing the Internet: The German Porn King's Revolutionary Model\">{{cite web|last1=Buse|first1=Uwe|title=Harnessing the Internet: The German Porn King's Revolutionary Model|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/zeitgeist/fabian-thylmann-and-his-revolutionary-porn-business-model-a-873802-2.html|website=Spiegel Online International|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013153311/http://www.spiegel.de/international/zeitgeist/fabian-thylmann-and-his-revolutionary-porn-business-model-a-873802-2.html|archivedate=13 October 2014|date=20 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2006 and 2010, Thylmann bought three more websites: [[MyDirtyHobby]], Webcams, and [[Xtube]].<ref name=\"The Geek-Kings of Smut page 5\" /> The domain name manwin.com was first registered in August 2007.<ref name=\"Whois manwin.com\">{{cite web|title=manwin.com registry whois|url=http://www.whois.com/whois/manwin.com|website=Whois|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219234106/http://www.whois.com/whois/manwin.com|archivedate=19 December 2014|date=19 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n;Acquisition of Mansef\nMansef was founded by [[Concordia University]] graduates Stephane Manos and Ouissam Youssef (Mansef a portmanteau of the two's surnames) in 2004 as the holding company for various \"[[thumbnail gallery post]]\" websites and an affiliate network. It later launched [[Brazzers]] and a porn production company among various other pa