to Record Crowd|last1=Hymes|first1=Tom|date=18 January 2012|website=AVN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526125810/http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-s-Fabian-Thylmann-Gives-Keynote-to-Record-Crowd-461103.html|archivedate=26 May 2013|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nManos and Youssef now run Valnet Inc. and Valsef Capital online media and investment companies of the Valsef Group. Valnet owns websites such as [[Screenrant.com]], [[CBR.com]], TheRichest.com among others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=241346392|title=Valnet Inc.: Private Company Information|website=bloomberg.com|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Valsef Capital: Private Company Information |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=241373444 |website=bloomberg.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=285956745&privcapId=241373444&previousCapId=241346392&previousTitle=Valnet%25252520Inc.|title=Ouissam Youssef: Executive Profile & Biography|website=bloomberg.com|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=285958185&privcapId=241373444|title=Stephane Manos: Executive Profile & Biography|website=www.bloomberg.com|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u2013present===\nIn April 2011, Manwin raised US$362 million in financing from Colbeck Capital, which Thylmann used to buy other pornographic companies such as [[Playboy TV]], [[Digital Playground]], [[Twistys]], [[YouPorn]], [[Redtube]], and Gaytube among others.<ref name=\"jonronson\" /><ref name=\"Vampire Porn\" /> Adult blogger/journalist [[Mike South]] initially broke the story as [[Fortress Investment Group]] (which was part of the investment) financing Manwin with US$168 million. [[Fox Business News]] reported on it in March 2013.<ref name=\"Manwin Says Its Porn Business is Legal\">{{cite web|last1=South|first1=Mike|title=Manwin Says Its Porn Business is Legal|url=https://video.foxbusiness.com/v/2235795190001/manwin-says-its-porn-business-is-legal/?#sp=show-clips}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2013, Thylmann sold his stake in Manwin to the senior management of the company, composed of Feras Antoon and David Tassilo, for $100 million,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.letagparfait.com/fr/2013/10/21/fabian-thylmann-revend-manwin-a-manwin/|title=Fabian Thylmann revend Manwin \u00e0 Manwin|last=Gonzo|first=|date=21 October 2013|work=Le Tag Parfait|access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Fabian Thylmann Sells Stake in Manwin to Company Management\">{{cite web|last1=Pardon|first1=Rhett|title=Fabian Thylmann Sells Stake in Manwin to Company Management|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=170250|website=XBIZ.com|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131025223413/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=170250|archivedate=25 October 2013|date=18 October 2013}}</ref> and later in the same month the company's name was changed to Mindgeek.<ref name=\"Manwin Becomes MindGeek\">{{cite web|title=Manwin Becomes MindGeek|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-Becomes-MindGeek-534744.html|website=AVN|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031202816/http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-Becomes-MindGeek-534744.html|archivedate=31 October 2013|date=28 October 2013}}</ref> This took place as Manwin and [[Redtube]], a very large porn tube site not in its network, merged.<ref name=\"Manwin Isnt Buying RedTube\">{{cite web|title=Manwin Isnt Buying RedTube|url=http://www.mikesouth.com/mike-south-commentary/manwin-isnt-buying-redtube-7916/|website=MikeSouth.com|accessdate=24 April 2016|date=31 July 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509080047/http://www.mikesouth.com/mike-south-commentary/manwin-isnt-buying-redtube-7916/|archivedate=9 May 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2013, Mindgeek's co-owner [[Feras Antoon]] and his brother Mark Antoon<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=http://plus.lapresse.ca/screens/32565496-c9b5-4da6-a548-a014bd80960f__7C___0.html|title=Un g\u00e9ant du XXX craint et admir\u00e9 - La Presse+|date=11 October 2016|work=La Presse+|access-date=3 June 2018|language=fr-CA}}</ref> were cited alongside the CEO of gaming technology giant [[Amaya Inc.]] and various of its own senior officers and stakeholders. The [[Autorit\u00e9 des march\u00e9s financiers (Qu\u00e9bec)|Quebec Market Authority]], the province's market regulator that is somewhat equivalent to the [[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission|U.S. SEC]], investigated [[Amaya Inc.|Amaya]]'s executives for trading on privileged information. According to the charges, some Mindgeek executives were found to have benefited from the leak of information, although they were not major players in the insider trading ring.<ref name=\"How Amaya CEO David Baazov went from high school dropout to running the world\u2019s biggest online poker room\">{{cite web|title=How Amaya CEO David Baazov went from high school dropout to running the world's biggest online poker room|url=http://business.financialpost.com/executive/how-amaya-ceo-david-baazov-went-from-high-school-dropout-to-running-the-worlds-biggest-online-poker-room|website=Financial Post|accessdate=25 April 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407203027/http://business.financialpost.com/executive/how-amaya-ceo-david-baazov-went-from-high-school-dropout-to-running-the-worlds-biggest-online-poker-room|archive-date=7 April 2016|date=23 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Timeline of acquisitions and partnerships===\n;June 2010\n:Manwin opened non-adult video sharing website Videobash.com (now defunct).<ref name=\"The Geek-Kings of Smut page 5\" />\n\n;September 2010\n:Manwin acquired EuroRevenue, which owned various niche pornography sites.<ref name=\"Manwin Takes Over EuroRevenue\">{{cite web|last1=Pardon|first1=Rhett|title=Manwin Takes Over EuroRevenue|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/125105|website=XBIZ|accessdate=20 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202223002/http://www.xbiz.com/news/125105|archivedate=2 December 2013|date=13 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n;November 2010\n:Manwin introduced celebrity news website Celebs.com (now defunct).<ref name=\"The Geek-Kings of Smut page 5\" />\n\n;December 2010\n:Manwin entered into a partnership with Wicked Pictures to manage Wicked Pictures' paysites.<ref name=\"Manwin to Manage Wicked Pictures\u2019 Online Properties\">{{cite web|title=Manwin to Manage Wicked Pictures' Online Properties|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-to-Manage-Wicked-Pictures-Online-Properties-420492.html|website=AVN|accessdate=20 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203031741/http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-to-Manage-Wicked-Pictures-Online-Properties-420492.html|archivedate=3 December 2013|date=28 December 2010}}</ref>\n\n;May 2011\n:Manwin acquired the pornographic video sharing website [[YouPorn]].<ref name=\"Manwin Acquires YouPorn.com\">{{cite web|title=Manwin Acquires YouPorn.com|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-Acquires-YouPorn-com-435351.html|website=AVN|accessdate=20 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140402042905/http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-Acquires-YouPorn-com-435351.html|archivedate=2 April 2014|date=10 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n;June 2011\n:Manwin bought all adult related assets of Carsed Marketing Incorporated, including [[Twistys]], Twistys Cash Affiliate Program, GayTube, SexTube, and TrannyTube.<ref name=\"Manwin Acquires Twistys and Sister Sites\" />\n\n;June 2011\n:Manwin created 3DXSTAR in a partnership with Funky Monkey Productions.<ref name=\"You Know You Want It: 3D Porn from Funky Monkey and Manwin\" />\n\n;November 2011\n:Manwin became an operating partner of [[Playboy]], managing the brand's online and entertainment business Playboy Plus Entertainment, which operates a number of television channels and online services based in the UK and Benelux.<ref name=\"Manwin takes over Playboy TV operations\">{{cite web|last1=Briel|first1=Robert|title=Manwin takes over Playboy TV operations|url=http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2011/10/31/manwin-takes-over-playboy-tv-operations/|website=Broadband TV News|accessdate=20 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203003713/http://www.broadbandtvnews.com/2011/10/31/manwin-takes-over-playboy-tv-operations/|archivedate=3 December 2013|date=31 October 2011}}</ref> Playboy CEO Scott Flanders later described the deal as \"the biggest mistake I've made at the company,\"<ref name=\"Playboy CEO\">{{cite web|last1=Shandrow|first1=Kim Lachance|title=Playboy CEO: Nudity Could Completely Vanish From the Brand|url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/240346|website=Entrepreneur|accessdate=14 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517042900/http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/240346|archivedate=17 May 2015|date=2 December 2014}}</ref> saying that \"Playboy should not have association with being in the sex-act business.\"<ref name=\"Playboy CEO\" /> In the spring of 2014, Playboy took back control of Playboy.com \"at significant expense\",<ref name=\"Playboy CEO\" /> although Mindgeek still retained control of Playboy TV and Playboy Plus, and Mindgeek still owns the Spice TV channels, which were also bought from Playboy.<ref name=\"Playboy CEO\" />\n\n;November 2011\n:Manwin launched Legendary Stats, a service that aggregates multiple affiliate programs and is targeted at affiliate site operators with large traffic volumes.<ref name=\"Manwin Launches Legendary Stats\">{{cite web|title=Manwin Launches Legendary Stats|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/technology/Manwin-Launches-Legendary-Stats-454459.html|website=AVN|accessdate=14 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217