ear-with-loss|title=Luxembourg Times - Luxembourg - Porn empire reports half billion dollars in revenue \u2013 but ends year with loss|website=luxtimes.lu|language=en|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> Its structure has been described as mostly a way to [[Tax avoidance|avoid corporate tax]] by a ''de facto'' Canadian company;<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.welt.de/print/wams/wirtschaft/article139749131/Seine-dreckigen-Hobbys.html|title=Seine dreckigen Hobbys|last=Pauly|first=Marcel|date=19 April 2015|work=DIE WELT|access-date=3 June 2018}}</ref> with billing companies in Ireland,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thejournal.ie/dublin-based-porn-firm-profits-3569482-Aug2017/|title=Dublin-based firm collects \u20ac356 million in revenue from porn subscriptions|last=Deegan|first=Gordon|work=TheJournal.ie|access-date=3 June 2018|language=en}}</ref> subsidiaries in Cura\u00e7ao and holding ones in Cyprus and Luxembourg, all countries that have been identified as tax havens or having lax tax regulations. Canada also has special tax treaties with Luxembourg, the legal headquarters of MindGeek, where a Canadian subsidiary is exempt from taxes paid on royalties to its Luxembourg parent.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nMost employees work at the headquarters in Montreal on [[:fr:Boulevard D\u00e9carie|D\u00e9carie Boulevard]], opposite the [[Orange Julep]], where more than 1,000 are employed.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n\n==Adult industry==\nIn 2013, the adult industry news website [[XBIZ]] described MindGeek as \"the largest adult entertainment operator globally\",<ref name=\"Fabian Thylmann Sells Stake in Manwin to Company Management\" /><ref name=\"Manwin Changes Name to MindGeek\">{{cite web|last1=Pardon|first1=Rhett|title=Manwin Changes Name to MindGeek|url=http://newswire.xbiz.com/view.php?id=170554|website=XBIZ Newswire|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114041749/http://newswire.xbiz.com/view.php?id=170554|archivedate=14 November 2013|date=28 October 2013}}</ref> and a spokesperson from Manwin, who spoke to the [[Irish Independent]] newspaper in 2013, stated that they are \"one of the top five bandwidth consumption companies in the world\".<ref name=\"Porn company Manwin latest Internet giant to open an office in Dublin\">{{cite web|title=Porn company Manwin latest Internet giant to open an office in Dublin|url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/porn-company-manwin-latest-internet-giant-to-open-an-office-in-dublin-209052071-237592411.html|website=IrishCentral|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219200119/http://www.irishcentral.com/news/porn-company-manwin-latest-internet-giant-to-open-an-office-in-dublin-209052071-237592411.html|archivedate=19 December 2014|date=27 May 2013}}</ref> The Internet pornography review site TheBestPorn.com lists 164 pornographic membership sites that are owned or represented by MindGeek.<ref name=\"Company: MindGeek TheBestPorn.com\">{{cite web|title=Company: MindGeek|url=http://www.thebestporn.com/review_company.html?id=2768|website=TheBestPorn.com|accessdate=20 December 2014|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6UxnU0TXz?url=http://www.thebestporn.com/review_company.html?id=2768|archivedate=20 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIt has been reported that MindGeek's dominance in online pornography may have negative results because of the monopolistic powers they have from owning both production and distribution avenues.<ref name=\"Vampire Porn\"/>\n\n===Pornhub Network===\nThe \"Pornhub Network\" is a network of [[web 2.0]] websites accessible through Mindgeek's [[PornMD]] search engine.<ref name=\"PornMD homepage\">{{cite web|title=PornMD: A Search Engine for ALL of the World's Best Porn Sites|url=http://www.pornmd.com/ |website=PornMD|accessdate=19 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141218050748/http://www.pornmd.com/ |archivedate=18 December 2014}}</ref> Mindgeek 