wire.xbiz.com/view.php?id=150413 |archivedate=30 June 2012 }}</ref> The website is categorized as glamcore, short for \"glamour hardcore\". The full-length videos are accessible to registered members. The website itself is considered important within the glamcore pornography sector. Glamcore typically features aesthetically appealing models; the film set includes natural lighting and high-definition cinematic elements that set it apart from traditional pornographic films. Babes.com is carefully run under the supervision of MindGeek so as to avoid all illegal activities. There are currently five major websites operating under Babes.com, which feature thematically different aspects in terms of settings and sexual preferences.<ref>{{cite web|title=Babes Network Sites|url=http://www.babes.com/tour/sites/|website=Babes|publisher=Mindgeek|accessdate=6 November 2016}}</ref> The Babes network is categorised not only by themes and videos (like most pornographic websites), but also by participating models and actresses.<ref>{{cite web|title=Models|url=http://www.babes.com/tour/models/|website=Babes|publisher=MindGeek|accessdate=6 November 2016}}</ref> As of November 2016, the Babes website had a global traffic ranking of 11,441.<ref>{{cite web|title=Babes.com Traffic, Demographics and Competitors|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/babes.com|website=Alexa|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=6 November 2016}}</ref> The website ranks as the third most-accessed site of MindGeek's network of porn sites.<ref>{{cite web|title=MindGeek Company Profile|url=http://www.thebestporn.com/review_company.html?id=2768|website=The Best Porn|publisher=TheBestPorn.com|accessdate=6 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Pornography for mobile devices===\nMindGeek's mobile pornography websites handle millions of visits each day in North America,<ref name=\"Life of a Porn \u2018Star': How This Montrealer Helped Build Adult Mobile, Part One\">{{cite web|last1=Czikk|first1=Joseph|title=Life of a Porn 'Star': How This Mo