ing on, and on |work=[[The Economist]] |url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/dailychart/2011/07/film-franchises |accessdate=4 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"CR: MGM\">\n{{cite web|title=Casino Royale (1967)|url=http://www.mgm.com/view/movie/342/Casino-Royale-(1967)|publisher=[[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]|accessdate=8 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"lost\">\n{{cite web|title=The Lost Bond|url=http://www.totalfilm.com/features/the-lost-bond|work=Total Film|publisher=[[Future Publishing]]|accessdate=13 October 2011|date=27 February 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MGM acq\">\n{{cite press release | title = Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Inc. announces acquisition of Never Say Never Again James Bond assets | publisher = [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]| date = 4 December 1997 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080505213137/http://mgm.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=47&printable|archivedate=5 May 2008| url = http://mgm.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=47&printable | accessdate = 16 March 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"NYT: Sony & MGM\">\n{{cite news|title=Sony Pictures, in an accord with MGM, drops its plan to produce new James Bond films|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=30 March 1999|url= https://www.nytimes.com/1999/03/30/business/media-business-advertising-sony-pictures-accord-with-mgm-drops-its-plan-produce.html?n=Top%2fNews%2fBusiness%2fSmall%20Business%2fMarketing%20and%20Advertising|accessdate=16 March 2008 | first=James | last=Sterngold}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: TND\">\n{{cite web|title=The 55th Annual Golden Globe Awards (1998)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1997|work=Golden Globe Awards|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=27 September 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130415020047/http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/1997|archivedate=15 April 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"GG: DAD\">\n{{cite web|title=The 60th Annual Golden Globe Awards (2003)|url=http://cdn.goldenglobes.org/browse/year/2002|work=Golde